9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 672, L.D. 1719, “An Act Regarding
10 Superintendent Agreements for Transfer Students”
11 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
12 following:
13 'Sec. 1. 20-A MRSA §5205, sub-§6, as amended by PL 2015, c. 448, §10, is further
14 amended to read:
15 6. Transfer students. The following provisions apply to transfers of students from
16 one school administrative unit to another.
17 A. Two superintendents may approve the transfer of a student from one school
18 administrative unit to another if the following conditions are satisfied:
19 (1) They find that a transfer is in the student's best interest; and
20 (2) The student's parent approves.
21 (3) The student's parent makes a written request to the superintendents of the
22 sending and receiving school administrative units concurrently. A request for a
23 transfer during the school year in which the request is made may be made at any
24 point during the year. A request for a transfer beginning the following school year
25 must be made after April 15th;
26 (4) The student's parent provides all evidence to support the request;
27 (5) The superintendent of the sending school administrative unit contacts the
28 superintendent of the receiving school administrative unit to discuss the transfer
29 prior to each superintendent making that superintendent's determination;
30 (6) The superintendents of the sending and receiving school administrative units
31 review the evidence provided pursuant to subparagraph (4), verify the information,
32 consider whether the transfer is in the best interest of the student and school
33 community and each individually decide to approve or deny the request; and
Page 1 - 132LR1437(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 672, L.D. 1719
1 (7) Each superintendent makes that superintendent's determination within 30
2 calendar days of receiving the transfer request.
3 The superintendents shall notify the commissioner of any transfer approved under this
4 paragraph. An approved transfer is in effect for the duration of the school year unless
5 the student's parent and both superintendents agree that reversing the transfer is in the
6 best interest of the student and school community. If either of the superintendents
7 decides not to approve the transfer, that the transfer is denied. Each superintendent
8 shall provide to the parent of the student requesting transfer under this paragraph a
9 written description of the basis of that superintendent's determination based on the
10 requirements of this paragraph. A transfer request may not be denied for the sole
11 reason that the student should attend school where the student's parent resides.
12 B. On the request of Within 15 calendar days of receiving the determinations of the
13 superintendents, the parent of a student requesting transfer under paragraph A, may
14 request that the commissioner shall review the transfer. The commissioner shall review
15 the superintendents' determinations evidence, information and documents provided
16 pursuant to paragraph A, subparagraphs (3) to (7) and may communicate with the
17 superintendents and with the parent of the student prior to making a decision. The
18 commissioner may approve or disapprove the transfer and shall provide to the parent
19 of the student and to the superintendents a written decision describing the basis of the
20 commissioner's determination. A transfer request may not be denied for the sole reason
21 that the student should attend school where the student's parent resides.
22 B-1. If both superintendents denied the transfer request, the commissioner shall review
23 only whether the superintendents reached their determinations in a way that was
24 arbitrary or unreasonable. In all other circumstances, the commissioner shall review
25 whether the transfer is in the best interest of the student and school community.
26 C. The superintendents shall annually review any transfer under this subsection.
27 D. For purposes of the state school subsidy, a student transferred under this subsection
28 is considered a resident of the school administrative unit to which transferred. Upon
29 request of the superintendent of schools in the unit in which a student is placed in
30 accordance with this subsection, the state share percentage for subsidized educational
31 costs for that student is equivalent to the state share percentage of the unit in which the
32 student's parent or legal guardian resides or the average state share percentage,
33 whichever is greater. If the parent or legal guardian does not reside in the State or can
34 not be located, the subsidy is the state average subsidy.
35 E. A school administrative unit may not charge tuition for a transfer approved under
36 this subsection.
37 F. If dissatisfied with the commissioner's decision, a parent of a student requesting
38 transfer or either superintendent may, within 10 15 calendar days of the commissioner's
39 decision, request that the state board review the transfer. The state board shall review
40 the superintendents' determinations and communicate with the commissioner, the
41 superintendents and the parent of the student only the documents and timelines required
42 in paragraph A and the written decision of the commissioner to the student's parent,
43 student and superintendents describing the basis of the commissioner's determination.
44 The state board may approve or disapprove the transfer. The state board shall make a
45 decision within 45 calendar days of receiving the request and shall provide to the parent
