416 of the student, the superintendents and the commissioner a written decision describing
427 the basis of the state board's determination. The state board's decision is final and
438 binding.
4 G. Notwithstanding paragraph D, if the commissioner or state board approves a
5 transfer under this subsection and the student subject to the transfer is receiving special
6 education services, the state subsidy of special education costs for the transferred
7 student may not be reduced as a result of the transfer.
8 A transfer under this subsection may not be made to a receiving school administrative unit
9 that does not operate a public school that includes the grade level of the student whose
10 parent requests the transfer, unless the superintendents of both the sending and receiving
11 school administrative units approve the transfer.'
12 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
13 number to read consecutively.
14 SUMMARY
1155 This amendment replaces the bill. The amendment establishes additional procedures
1166 for certain transfer students. The amendment provides that 2 superintendents may approve
1177 the transfer of a student from one school administrative unit to another if the student's
1188 parent provides evidence to support the request, the superintendents discuss and review the
1199 transfer evidence and whether the transfer is in the best interest of the student and school
2200 community and the superintendents decide on the transfer within 30 days of receiving the
2211 request. The amendment also establishes additional procedures for the appeal of a denied
2222 transfer request to the Commissioner of Education and the State Board of Education and
2233 provides that a transfer request may not be denied for the sole reason that the student should
2244 attend school where the student's parent resides.
